Police at JKIA on Wednesday intercepted a consignment of Pangolin scales which were on transit to Bangkok, Thailand. A police officer, who requested anonymity, said that the scales weighed 100 kilos and are worth at least Sh60 million."The consignment was on transit from Yaounde Cameroon," the officer said.Airport police boss could not be reached for comment.Details about the owner of the consignment are yet to be established.In June, KWS officers seized 500 kilogrammes of pangolin scales at the Jomo Kenyatta International AirportRead: KWS intercepts 500 kilogrammes of pangolin scales at JKIA